   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ASSESS (Moscow) _ A news analysis. The method to
Yeltsin's apparent madness of yet another government shakeup:
self-protection. His prime minister was in bed with his enemies, he
came in as political stabilizer but was unable for last three
months to control the growing impeachment drive and the conflict
with Parliament over Yeltsin's desire to remove Russia's chief
prosecutor. By Michael Wines.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-STEPASHIN (Moscow) _ A profile of Sergei Stepashin, the
new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-POLITICS (Jerusalem) _ Russian immigrants are now the
king-makers of Israeli politics, and this group that can swing the
election either way is moving away from Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   ITALY-POLITICS (Rome) _ On Thursday, the Italian Parliament will
begin selecting Italy's next president, largely a figurehead. But
rather than a dull civics exercise, the process is full of mystery
and intrigue, closely watched by Italians. By Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-STEINBERG (New York) _ Saul Steinberg, the metaphysically
minded artist and cartoonist and brooding doodler whose drawings
appeared in The New Yorker for more than half a century, elevating
comic illustration into fine art, died Wednesday at his home in
Manhattan. He was 84. By Sarah Boxer.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-HATECRIME (Austin, Texas) _ Strange things happen to a
state legislative session when the governor is a front-runner in
the next presidential election, which may be why a hate crimes bill
named in honor of the black man who was dragged to death by whites
in East Texas has unexpectedly emerged as one of the most
emotional, political flashpoints of the current session. By Rick
Lyman.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-LIPOSUCTION-RISK (New York) _ A team of doctors in New York
is questioning the safety of liposuction, the popular cosmetic
surgery in which body fat is vacuumed out through a tube. The
doctors' warning, to be published in the New England Journal of
Medicine, is based on their review of five deaths that occurred in
New York after liposuction from 1993 to 1998. By Denise Grady.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AGING-GENES (Undated) _ The Discovery of a new gene in the
C. elegans roundworm suggests an interesting link between its
life-lengthening genes and a leading theory of human aging, the
belief that cells age through oxidative stress as reactive
chemicals attack DNA. By Nicholas Wade.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUBIN-SUMMERS (Washington) _ Deputy Treasury Secretary Lawrence
Summers, who was nominated on Wednesday to succeed Treasury
Secretary Robert Rubin, arrived in Washington six years ago with a
reputation for brilliance and an equal reputation for intolerance
of those he considered slow to grasp the dynamics of an unforgiving
global economy. But in the past year or two, a new Larry Summers
has emerged _ one who has tamed his sharp-edged wit, who regularly
solicits key congressmen and senators for their advice, who now
occasionally admits to errors of political judgment. By David E.
Sanger.
</P>
