<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ When I heard about storyteller
and journalist Dr. Americo Paredes' death, I thought about what
Miles Davis once said about Duke Ellington: ``I think all musicians
should get together on a certain day and get down on their knees
and thank Duke.'' Similarly, today's crop of Mexican American
journalists should get down on their knees and thank Dr. Paredes.
(Garcia, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Bush stalling on hate-crimes
bill, but other lawmakers are undecided or unsupportive, too.
(McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ OPTIONS is a place where students
who felt marginalized on their home campuses feel more mainstream.
Whether the issue is social promotion, whether it's social
alienation, school districts that want to do the right thing will
offer options. Or they'll simply let those at the margins drift off
the edge. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
