   KOSOVO-STRIKES _ WASHINGTON _ The latest developments in the
NATO air campaign against Yugoslavia, and the diplomatic efforts to
halt the bombing. Developing. (Deans, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ As Congress continued work on a
pork-laden bill to pay for the Kosovo war, President Clinton on
Thursday welcomed the prospect of having the $11.7 billion measure,
even if it was twice the amount he sought. House-Senate negotiators
were expected to resume work Thursday afternoon. (Malone, Cox News
Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   ALBANIA-CAMP _ TIRANA, Albania _ The first American camp opens
in Albania to house 20,000 refugees. First lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton is expected to visit on Friday. Developing. (Roughton, Cox
News Service). 20. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-APACHE _ RINAS AIR FIELD, Albania _ How Johnny Ringo
decided on the spot that although he, too, could smell gasoline
coming from one of the refueling tankers for Apache attack
helicopters here minutes before a mission, he'd go for it. There
literally wasn't time to check with superiors. And how he got there
in time, with 10 seconds to spare, to refuel the roughly 10 Apaches
as they floated in like black ghosts to meet the Chinook.
(Albright, Cox News Service). 20. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
