<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORSE-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DEALIN' WILLIE WANTS YOUR WHEELS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ROB MORSE  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ San Francisco Mayor Willie Brown is getting
weird on us. I'm not talking about micro-management, like issuing
orders to branch librarians about preschool reading programs.
</P>
<P>
   I say promote the 11-year-old boy who wants to read to little
kids for a half-hour a week in the library. I don't know if he's
the Reading Wizard, as he claims, but he's the Wizard of Spin.
</P>
<P>
   How'd he like to be mayor?
</P>
<P>
   No, micro-managing and issuing edicts are not weird for Brown.
</P>
<P>
   What's weird is all the stuff he's trying to take away from
people, from shopping carts to cars. He's willing to take any kind
of vehicle from the despised of the Earth, as long as it's a
vehicle for his re-election.
</P>
<P>
   Brown is going to be re-elected as mayor anyway, but he's still
running scared. He may not prove as popular with voters as he is
with himself.
</P>
<P>
   Sometimes it's hell having an ego as big as the Ritz.
</P>
<P>
   Especially when most voters want to check out.
</P>
<P>
   So now we have government by confiscation _ and not just
confiscating tax money to pour into City Hall sinkholes.
</P>
<P>
   It looks like he'll never get those shopping carts out of the
clutches of the homeless, so now he has another election-eve ploy.
He wants to take cars from people arrested for allegedly soliciting
prostitutes or buying drugs.
</P>
<P>
   The mayor sees a threat to the city from degenerate
out-of-towners in BMWs. As if there aren't enough degenerate San
Franciscans, in BMWs or otherwise. But now we have to talk about
outside agitators for degenerateness.
</P>
<P>
   Great city forced to import degenerates.
</P>
<P>
   I wonder how many official city cars will be seized. If such a
law existed a few years ago, a few high elected officials I won't
name would have been doing a lot of walking.
</P>
<P>
   So here we have this allegedly liberal city that's going fascist
on us, and worse, getting its ideas from Oakland. The city is going
to seize and hold people's property before they've been convicted
of anything.
</P>
<P>
   I had to check the World Almanac to see if the Constitution had
changed.
</P>
<P>
   No, it's still there in the Fifth Amendment, the thing about how
no person shall be ``deprived of life, liberty, or property,
without due process of law.''
</P>
<P>
   But heck, by the time the courts sort it out, the election will
be over.
</P>
<P>
   &QC;   &QC;
</P>
<P>
   This from the Irish end of the Internet: ``News flash: White
House _ President Clinton announced today an all-out bombing
offensive against England will begin in two weeks, unless a peace
accord is ratified by England and its break-away province of
Northern Ireland.''
</P>
<P>
   That was a joke, Guinness-fueled. This is not a joke: Gloria La
Riva, our favorite perennial leftist candidate for governor, is off
to Belgrade with Ramsey Clark, the former attorney general. La Riva
is taking a video camera and says she's going to document ``U.S.
genocide against the Serbs.''
</P>
<P>
   I asked how long she'll be gone. ``Until Thursday,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   I don't know if that's enough time to cover a genocide, but I
think she meant next Thursday. I wished her luck, and told her to
stay away from embassies.
</P>
<P>
   &QC;   &QC;  I'm more of the school that the United States is committing
stupidicide in the Balkans. The accidental bombing of the Chinese
embassy is so stupid it must make Clinton crazy, given how much
he's sucked up to the Chinese.
</P>
<P>
   If he wants to bomb a Chinese facility, why not hit Los Alamos?
The U.S. technical blunder in bombing the embassy sends a clear
message to the Chinese: Maybe those bomb secrets they stole from
the United States aren't so valuable after all.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
