   FILM-DANCEMAKER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Dancemaker,'' the Oscar-nominated documentary about
choreographer Paul Taylor, starts with a camera watching from the
wings as his company bounds onto the stage. As we hear the dancers
sliding across the floor and their footfalls slapping onto the
boards, ``Dancemaker's'' uniqueness is evident. Never before has a
movie on dancers given such a sense of their physcial presence. And
we also get a sense of the man who created the company, and whose
talent and ego have made it such a singular artistic triumph. By
ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
