   FILM-THE CASTLE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Some of the hype for the gently satirical comedy ``The
Castle'' is trying to cast director/co-writer Rob Sitch as an
Australian Roberto Benigni. But the comparison is mostly specious:
Sitch's dry, deadpan approach couldn't be more different from
Benigni's manic romanticism. Both styles do have the potential to
divide audiences, but not in the same ways. Like Benigni with
``Life Is Beautiful,'' Sitch uses comedy in an attempt to explore
some serious subjects. And like Benigni, he's concocted a very
likable family with an eccentric patriarch. By ROBERT PHILPOT.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
