   UNDATED _ The names Bernie Marcus and Arthur Blank may not be
familiar to you, but if you're a homeowner, you sure know their
store. I'm talking about the suburbanite's main supplier. The place
new homeowners go and drop a hundred bucks every week for what
seems like years and never think twice. I'm talking about Home
Depot. If you ever wondered how such a great concept developed, or
how much a retailer could influence American life, read ``Built
from Scratch: How A Couple of Regular Guys Grew The Home Depot From
