<HEADER>
A6029 &Cx1f; tic-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SWEETSIDE-FOOD-AZR &LR;      05-13 0299
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SWEETSIDE-FOOD-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOW TO CARAMELIZE ONIONS  
 (ADV: WITH SWEETONIONS-FOOD) 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JUDY WALKER  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Caramelizing onions:
</P>
<P>
   1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. &QL; 
2. Line bottom of heavy-duty baking pan with unbleached parchment
paper. This eliminates scorching and the need to grease the pan. If
you don't use parchment paper, be prepared to spend time cleaning
the baking surface. &QL; 
3. Clean onions by cutting off the tops and roots. Cut through the
outer layer of onion skin to get a good clean onion. &QL; 
4. Cut onions into 3/4 - to 1-inch slices. &QL; 
5. Place onions side by side (do not layer) on the parchment. &QL; 
6. Brush slices with 1/4 cup good-quality olive oil. Sprinkle with
freshly ground black pepper and salt to taste. &QL; 
7. Cover pan and bake for 45 minutes. &QL; 
8. Turn onions with a spatula, then repeat steps 6 and 7. Total
baking time should be about 90 minutes. &QL; 
9. For last 30 minutes, remove cover so liquid evaporates. &QL; 
10. Remove and serve immediately, or keep warm at a low temperature
until serving time. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NOTE: Onions may look dark brown or even black. This is
caramelization. &QL; 
To freeze the caramelized onions, deglaze with water. Remove
onions, add a little water on top of the parchment paper to loosen
the residue, and scrape residue from parchment paper into a small
bag to freeze. &QL; 
Put onion slices in freezer bags. &QL; 
To remove fat: Pour deglazing liquid into a separate container and
chill until the oil can be removed. Then freeze remaining liquid. &QL; 
Caramelized onion slices also can be pureed in a blender and
frozen. Use the puree (and any deglazing liquid) in small amounts
to enliven any dish, from chili to soups to omelets to salad
dressings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Source: Ken Gablin. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
