   w/
</P>
<P>
   HKN-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Buffalo, N.Y.) _ Buffalo. It is 400
miles from everywhere and when you get there . . . there's nothing.
By Dan Shaughnessy.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-SABRES-WARD (Buffalo, N.Y.) _ For players who inhabit the
NHL fringes, such as Sabres winger Dixon Ward, insecurity is such a
staple that it becomes almost a comfort zone. By Bob Duffy.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NY-MIAMI (New York) _ Pat Riley's practices can be tests of
will, stamina and purpose. Thursday's was also a chance for the
game's eminent coaching mind to remind his bruised forces that it
might be their last get-together for quite awhile. By Peter May.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-SARAZEN (Undated) _ Gene Sarazen, the first golfer to win
all four of the sport's major championships, is dead. He was 97. By
Jim McCabe.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
