<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Friday, May 14, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   BURBANK-AIRPORT (Los Angeles) _ Burbank Airport must apply for a
mandatory curfew on night flights and other noise retrictions, FAA
officials said Thursday in a ruling that has infuriated city
officials. By Lee Condon. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   MIRACLE RECOVERY (Los Angeles) _ Keith Mullins wasn't expected
to live after a car driven by an alleged drunk driver plowed into
his in a Jan. 15 accident. Mullins, the 54-year-old business owner
and president of the Mid-Valley Chamber of Commerce, sustained a
head injury and multiple fractures and remained in a coma. Then
suddenly and unexpectedly, Mullins woke up, five weeks after the
accident. And on Saturday, he is expected to go home. By Robert
Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   HATE-CRIMES (Los Angeles) _ A report issued today by the county
Commission on Human Relations recommends steps to combat hate
crimes, including a media campaign aimed at children, who are
viewed as a fertile audience for messages promoting harmony and
tolerance. By Douglas Haberman. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
