<HEADER>
A6151 &Cx1f; tad-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS12-C     05-13 0723
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS12-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Augusta _ The 10th annual Riverwalk Acoustic &AMP; Bluegrass
Festival on Saturday at the Jessye Norman Amphitheatre downtown
features Avalanche, Flatbed, Andy McCraw, Cedar Hill, the Flowers
Family and Steel Blue. 706-592-0054.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Macon _ ``Such Beautiful Things _ Highlights From the Hay
Porcelain Collection'' will be exhibited Friday through July 18 at
the Hay House, an 1859 Italianate Revival mansion that is a museum.
912-742-8155.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Jackson _ The Heart of Georgia Fine Arts Festival is Saturday
on the grounds of the Carmichael House. While more than 30 artists
display their work in the juried art show outside, tours of the
1897 Victorian mansion, listed on the National Register of Historic
Places, will be available. Box lunches available. Rain date:
Sunday. 770-775-1696.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Summerville _ The 15th annual Howard Finster Art Exhibit, with
many of the artist's earlier works, will be at the First National
Bank through Saturday. 706-857-3473. The Finster Fest, featuring 50
folk artists, handmade instruments and musicians and singers from
