<P>
   BOEING-CUTS (Seattle) _ Boeing announced Thursday that it will
eliminate at least 7,000 of 20,000 jobs in St. Louis by the middle
of 2001 as production of the F-15 and F-18 fighters come to a halt.
This all means that Boeing could end next year with more than
53,000 fewer workers than at its peak last July.
</P>
