Bainbridge Island, Wash., died Thursday after a lengthy bout with
cancer. Greenfield was a Seattle native who attained to an
insider's perch in Washington, D.C., but brought to it an
independence and detachment, and moved late in life to re-establish
ties with the place where she grew up.
</P>
<P>
