</P>
<P>
   ORPHAN-REUNION (Seattle) _ More than 40 years ago, Tina Wright
was taken from her poor, Greek family to be temporarily cared for
in an orphanage. The country was rebuilding after being ravaged by
World War II and a civil war. Under these chaotic circumstances
9-month-old Constantia, her given name, was illegally sent to the
United States to be adopted by a Seattle couple. This was the only
family Wright knew until this Easter when her Greek mother and
sisters contacted her after decades of searching for their lost
baby.
</P>
<P>
