   PHONE-COMPETITION (Seattle) _ Telephone consumers may not know
it, but all heck is breaking loose around them. Not only are US
West, MCI, and AT&AMP;T engaged in a fierce mudslinging campaign in the
fight for customers, but the very ground upon which the companies
fight is shifting. Wireless telephone service continues to take a
big bite out of traditional copper-wire telephone service. Soon,
cable television will get into the act. And computers and the
Internet also are getting into the telephone game.
</P>
<P>
   By Jane Hadley. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   SMITH-WORKPLACE-COLUMN (Undated) _ If the idea of giving
speeches gives you quaky knees and nightmares, Geoffrey Lane has
