<HEADER>
A6196 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CAR-NASCAR-NOTES-COX     05-13 0501
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-NASCAR-NOTES-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Nascar notebook: Keller grabs pole position
 &HT;    By Al Levine
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Richmond, Va. _ Jason Keller hopes to have his No. 57 Chevrolet
headed in the right direction in tonight's Hardee's 250 Busch race.
He'll be starting out in good shape, on the pole, after Thursday's
record-busting qualifying lap.
</P>
<P>
   Keller whipped around the resurfaced three-quarter-mile asphalt
track at Richmond International Speedway in a track-record 124.907
mph (21.616 seconds) to steal the pole from Winston Cup veteran
Mark Martin.
</P>
<P>
   Martin had broken the track record nearly an hour earlier
Thursday but lost the prime spot to Keller, the 54th of 57 drivers
attempting to make the field.
</P>
<P>
   Keller, who has two poles, one win and five top 10s in 11 Busch
races, said life is wonderful if you have a fast car. He is having
a good year after placing in the top five just twice in 31 races
last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't forget how to drive last year and then just wake up
and remember how to do this over the winter,'' Keller said. ``It's
a lot easier to drive fast cars than it is slow cars.''
</P>
<P>
   This is his second pole since 1994 at Richmond and his second
track record. But he hasn't won here yet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've come across the checkered flag sideways, backwards and
wrecked,'' Keller said. ``I think if I do that, I'm not going to
win. If I come across the checkered flag straight, I'm going to
win.''
</P>
<P>
   Martin was one of seven Winston Cup drivers to make the top 25
Thursday. Twelve tried to win a spot in the race.
</P>
<P>
   Little E hits the wall
</P>
<P>
   Busch points leader Dale Earnhardt Jr. went to a backup car and
qualified fourth Thursday after putting his car into the wall
during practice. The wreck happened between turns three and four.
</P>
<P>
   ``The track's real slick, I don't know why it happened,''
Earnhardt said. ``I don't know anything about sealers and asphalt,
good or bad. I saw a couple of cars that were loose. We were loose
and maybe we should have come in and tried to fix it.''
</P>
<P>
   Earnhardt crashed with 10 laps to go in last week's Busch race
in New Hampshire when another got into the back of his after his
No. 3 Chevrolet lost the rear end. He finished 34th. He finished
second and first in two races at Richmond last year.
</P>
<P>
   Tony Stewart is engaged
</P>
<P>
   Winston Cup rookie Tony Stewart's engagement was announced
Thursday by a public relations firm in Harrisburg, N.C. The release
said: ``Dr. Daniel and Phylis (cq) Dwyer of Rockville, Ind., are
pleased to announce the engagement of their daughter, Krista, to
Tony Stewart, son of Mrs. Pam Boas of Dayton, Ind., and Nelson
Stewart of Indianapolis.''
</P>
<P>
   The bride-to-be is the marketing and recruiting director of an
Indianpolis medical firm. The groom-to-be drives the No. 20
Pontiac. Cup teams arrive here Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Al Levine writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution, Atlanta,
Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
