<HEADLINE>
USC ADDS TO POINT-GUARD MIX
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC's search for help at the point-guard position
continued Thursday when the Trojans signed junior college transfer
Rashad Jones of San Jose Community College to a national letter of
intent.
</P>
<P>
   Jones attended San Jose CC the past two seasons. He averaged
15.7 points, 6.0 assists and 3.1 steals last year.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-2 Jones will serve as the backup to sophomore Brandon
Granville. USC will also add a walk-on point guard in the fall,
Ryan Miller of New Albany, Ind.
</P>
<P>
   USC has one scholarship available. The Trojans previously signed
6-4 shooting guard Nate Hair of Capistrano Valley, 7-3 center Luke
Minor of Dyke, Va., and 6-11 center Konstantinos Charissis of
Greece.
</P>
</TEXT>
