Hiss, son of Alger Hiss, in New York last week. In a potentially
groundbreaking ruling that could help resolve some of the enduring
mysteries of the cold war, a Federal judge in Manhattan on Thursday
ordered the government to unseal thousands of pages of secret grand
jury testimony from the investigation of Alger Hiss and the
underground Communist movement in the United States. Hiss said his
father would have been ``thrilled by this decision.'' (Fred R.
