passenger waits for an American Airlines flight in February at
O'Hare Airport. The Federal government on Thursday accused American
Airlines, the nation's second largest carrier, of temporarily
slashing prices and increasing flights to drive low-cost carriers
out of its Texas hub. The antitrust case is the first predatory
pricing action brought by the Justice Department against an airline
since the industry was deregulated 21 years ago. (Todd Buchanan/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
