words because they are offensive or cruel, perhaps this carries
things too far into dishonesty. Ethnic cleansing is genocide and it
should be referred to as such. Because Nazis used the phrase ``The
Final Solution'' to describe the murder of millions of Jews, it did
not make it easier on those being murdered.
 &HT;    To me, euphemisms are amusing only when they are not used to
cover or disguise an evil deed. Winston Churchill could have told
you that.
 &HT;    
 c. 1999 Tim Giago 
<TEXT>
 &UR; NEW AMERICA NEWS SERVICE &QC; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QC;
