<SLUG> BC-ETOYS-UNVEILED-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW GAME TITLES UNVEILED AT ELECTRONIC ENTERTAINMENT EXPO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ With offerings from cyber-bowlers to stealth
fighters, digirati made a strong showing at the Electronic
Entertainment Expo's return to Los Angeles, with game makers THQ
Inc. and NovaLogic unveiling nine new titles between them.
</P>
<P>
   At the Thursday opening of E3, the multimedia industry's largest
annual gathering, attention firmly focused on the launch of several
``Star Wars''-related video games. And THQ, for one, has a hand in
the ``Phantom Menace'' juggernaut. It is the primary games
distributor in Germany, Austria and Switzerland for Lucasarts, the
game company owned by ``Star Wars'' creator George Lucas.
</P>
<P>
   But like rival NovaLogic, THQ emphasized its proprietary titles
in a preview Wednesday. And in a move that could help its Wall
Street standing, the company took special care to promote its
nonwrestling products. Despite strong earnings growth, THQ stock
has performed sluggishly in recent quarters with investors
apparently still concerned over the loss of the license to market
games under the WCW title beginning this summer to industry
behemoth Electronic Arts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wall Street doesn't understand we're not just about
wrestling,'' THQ Chief Executive Brian Farrel said, adding that it
has successful titles in the children's segment, sports and
adventure games. ``I don't think the market understands that yet.''
</P>
<P>
   For its first-round of E3 launches,THQ unveiled Felony Pursuit,
an urban driving police chase; Brunswick Circuit Pro Bowling, a new
title for the Nintendo 64; Toy Story 2, a collaboration with Walt
Disney Co. based on the coming movie; and Championship Motocross, a
motorcycle simulator endorsed by two-time national champion Ricky
Carmichael.
</P>
<P>
   Analyst Stewart Halpern at ING Baring Furman Selz said THQ's E3
performance is winning the company accolades and should translate
into a higher price for the stock. ``It looks like they're going to
be a big winner at this show,'' Halpern said. ``They've come out
with great momentum.''
</P>
<P>
   THQ shares rose to $27.5625 Wednesday, up $1.6875.
</P>
<P>
   For its part, privately held NovaLogic, also of Calabasas,
presented five new titles _ four of them sequels _ including a
World War II flying game, a tank battle game based on the M-1A2
Abrams main battle tank, a helicopter flight simulator and a flight
simulator based on the F-22 fighter.
</P>
<P>
   Novalogic's one entirely new title, JSF, is a combat flight
simulator based on Lockheed Martin's stealthy joint strike fighter
design.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
